    <item>
      <title>MDM2</title>
      <link>/genepanel/4193/info/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 05 May 2019 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>/genepanel/4193/info/</guid>
      <description>


&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MDM2 proto-oncogene&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;left&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENTREZID: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/4193&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;4193&lt;/a&gt; | Type: Protein Coding |
Map: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genome/gdv/browser/gene/?id=4193&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt; 12q15&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
OMIM: &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/610988&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;610988&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/608446&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;608446&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/607507&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;607507&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/153440&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;153440&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;justify&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Summary Entrez&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;This gene encodes a nuclear-localized E3 ubiquitin ligase. The encoded protein can promote tumor formation by targeting tumor suppressor proteins, such as p53, for proteasomal degradation. This gene is itself transcriptionally-regulated by p53. Overexpression or amplification of this locus is detected in a variety of different cancers. There is a pseudogene for this gene on chromosome 2. Alternative splicing results in a multitude of transcript variants, many of which may be expressed only in tumor cells. [provided by RefSeq, Jun 2013] &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
</description>
